 blinking sources can significantly increase the localisation precision
 compared to the static situation.
 This effect is stronger for close (
\begin_inset Formula $d<50\ \text{nm}$
\end_inset

) and bright (
\begin_inset Formula $\Lambda>1000\ \text{photons}$
\end_inset

) sources with lower background levels (
\begin_inset Formula $bg<100$
\end_inset

).
